    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-14T10:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-14T10:29:00-05:00" n="592"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d592">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2202</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]<note n="3" xml:id="d592fn3">Printed
                            in full, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>
                            <ref target="#pg_211">p. 211</ref>.</note>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-14T20:00:00+04:31">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 14, 1918, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received July 4, 6.07 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>269. … French Minister for Foreign Affairs cables French Embassy here that
                    military conference Paris, June 3, decided to hold Murman first, then Archangel,
                    if impossible simultaneously, and to land battalions American, British, French,
                    Italian troops with necessary munitions and provisions to hold those ports, all
                    troops being under British command until otherwise ordered. …</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
